quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  21,91,"And she who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her of Our Spirit and made her and her son a sign to<i class=""s"">(all people of) </i>all realms."
  21,92,"Indeed, this community of yours<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>is one community and I am your Lord, so worship Me."
  21,93,"But they tore themselves into sects; they are all returning to Us."
  21,94,"So whoever does righteous deeds and is a believer—his endeavor will never be denied. And indeed, We are writing it down for him."
  21,95,"And there is a ban on any town that We have annihilated—that they do not return,"
  21,96,"until, when Gog and Magog are <span class=""h"">opened<sup foot_note=""80583"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, and they swarm down from every mound,"
  21,97,"and the true promise has drawn near— then, the sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>of those who denied glaze over: “Woe to us. We have been oblivious to this. Rather, we were unjust.”"
  21,98,"You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and what you worship apart from Allah are indeed fuel for Hell. You are bound to approach it."
  21,99,"Had these been gods, they would not have approached it. And all will abide in it."
  21,100,"In it they wail, and in it they do not hear."
  21,101,"Indeed, those who deserved goodness from Us—those are kept away from it."
